[
    {
        "content": "<p>so in Elm, <code>elm-format</code> formats lists like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I wrote the original design doc for <code>elm-format</code>, and my reasoning for this design was to be consistent with the vertical style, which was this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>so the idea was that there would consistently be a space between the opening brace and the first element, regardless of whether it was written vertically or horizontally</p>",
        "id": 276956958,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528134
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in Roc, our vertical format looks like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276956977,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528168
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so we could do the horizontal style either way:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276957032,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528210
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in a couple of weeks I'm gonna give a fairly extended demo of <code>examples/gui</code>, so I figured I'd bring this up now before then in case it makes sense to change</p>",
        "id": 276957061,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528273
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>one of the implications of this would be that it would impact type annotations as well, so for example the type of <code>List.get</code> would change:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">get</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">OutOfBounds</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">get</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">OutOfBounds</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276957077,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528315
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't have a strong preference either way on <code>[ a, b, c ]</code> vs <code>[a, b, c]</code> but I do like the error type being more compact in <code>get</code></p>\n<p>of note, I think it's important to be consistent on these - so if lists are compact, records should be too - e.g. <code>{x, y, z}</code> over <code>{ x, y, z }</code> - as should imports and such in module headers</p>",
        "id": 276957133,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528360
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>curious what others think!</p>",
        "id": 276957137,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528367
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am partial to adding the space. Just find that I have been adding it to my code (tags and lists) cause it makes things slightly more readable to me, but no major opinion.</p>",
        "id": 276957155,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1648528393
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I find I want it most with tags that have type variables: <code>[Err a]</code> just reads weird to me without the spaces</p>",
        "id": 276957220,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1648528465
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or worse: <code>[T a b]</code> or <code>[T (Dict k v) b]</code></p>",
        "id": 276957228,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1648528490
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>is that only if it's a single tag?</p>\n<p>e.g. how do you feel about these?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">Bool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">True</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">False</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ok</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">Bool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">True</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">False</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ok</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">err</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276957347,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648528672
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I still likely it slightly better with the space. I guess it also depends a lot of the syntax coloring though.</p>",
        "id": 276958128,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1648529788
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By making the brackets hide more with coloring, space or not matters even less.</p>",
        "id": 276958141,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1648529818
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe this means the brackets in my color scheme are too bold so I want the space.</p>",
        "id": 276958150,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1648529845
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>would this affect parenthesis as well? <code>someFunc (someOtherFunc \"hello\")</code> vs <code>someFunc ( someOtherFunc \"hello\" )</code>. If not then maybe that could be an argument for no spaces for <code>[]</code> or <code>{}</code> as well</p>",
        "id": 276958520,
        "sender_full_name": "Jared Cone",
        "timestamp": 1648530174
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not having a space would simplify things for the editor because I wouldn't need to add or remove spaces for multi-line vs single-line vs empty lists/records. Although in design in general, having more spacing between elements is nicer to look at.</p>",
        "id": 276966388,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1648538328
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm confident people will get used to it either way, just as you see people get used to reading code when you take away token-based syntax highlighting in favor of a more useful contextual colorization.</p>",
        "id": 277010413,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1648563166
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we add more spacing we should also (I believe) encourage formatting styles that keep elements together: perhaps give your error union a name instead of wrapping it over multiple lines, or have a consistent roc-format convention for a multi line annotation when it doesn't fit within however many characters on a single line</p>",
        "id": 277010851,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1648563358
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"481285\">Jared Cone</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/formatting.20spaces.20around.20collection.20literals/near/276958520\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>would this affect parenthesis as well? <code>someFunc (someOtherFunc \"hello\")</code> vs <code>someFunc ( someOtherFunc \"hello\" )</code>. If not then maybe that could be an argument for no spaces for <code>[]</code> or <code>{}</code> as well</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>personally I don't think parens should have spaces regardless. (They don't currently.)</p>",
        "id": 277012898,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648564147
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Agreed. Then that could be a minor argument for not using spaces for the other brackets. I'm in the same boat as everyone else where I don't really care, just trying to think of some logic for one way or the other :)</p>",
        "id": 277019819,
        "sender_full_name": "Jared Cone",
        "timestamp": 1648566756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>seems like this is a minor enough consideration either way that it's not worth changing anything; I'll plan to do the demo with the current formatting! <span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span></p>",
        "id": 277039228,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1648574787
    }
]